7 An Act relating to real property; authorizing use of
certain contingency for real estate contracts for
8 municipalities, counties, and the state; providing
for codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 43-116 of Title 11, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A municipality may enter into a real estate contract for the
16 sale, conveyance, or exchange of real property, option to purchase
17 real property, or a lease with an option to purchase real property
18 that includes a contingency, not to exceed one hundred eighty (180)
19 days, for the purposes of securing required permits, lot changes,
20 zoning changes, and any other land use approvals necessary to use
21 and operate the real property.
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 865.70 of Title 19, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
